This paper focuses on learning visual representations using spatial context as a self-supervisory signal. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks for learning, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions unsupervised feature learning, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of pre-trained models and model initialization suggests that it could also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses object categorization and detection, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
